China Stocks: East-China Computer, Huaxia Bank, Nanjing Port

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-08-12T04:11:38Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-12/citic-cnr-datong-coal-huaxia-ping-an-china-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in China trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 11:30 a.m. local time break.  The Shanghai Composite Index, which tracks the bigger of
China’s stock exchanges, gained 13.53 points, or 0.5 percent, to
2,595.04. The  CSI 300 Index (SHSZ300)  rose 0.5 percent to 2,880.96.  Technology stocks: Shanghai East-China Computer Co. (600850
CH), a Shanghai-based computer product provider, surged by its
10 percent daily limit to 20.34 yuan, set for the biggest gain
since Nov. 4, 2010.  Neusoft Corp. (600718)  (600718 CH), a software maker,
jumped 7.3 percent to 10.77 yuan, on course for the largest gain
since September 13. Shandong Inspur Software Co. (600756 CH)
rose 6.9 percent to 12.23 yuan.  China will expand the imports of advanced technology, key
equipment and parts as it will push developed countries to ease
restrictions on high-tech products exports to China, Li Rongcan,
an assistant commerce minister, said at a forum in Beijing
today, according to a webcast on sina.com.  Huaxia Bank Co. (600015 CH), partly owned by Deutsche Bank
AG, rose 2.2 percent to 10.05 yuan, heading for the biggest gain
in a month after the company said first-half net income jumped
42 percent from a year ago to 4.3 billion yuan.  Nanjing Port Co. (002040 CH), a port operator in Jiangsu,
rose 1.3 percent to 7.69 yuan. The port operator said first-half
net income rose 63 percent from a year earlier to 21 million
yuan.  XCMG Construction Machinery Co. (000425 CH),  China ’s
biggest crane maker, added 1.8 percent to 21.7 yuan, setting for
the biggest gain since July 1. The company said first-half net
income rose 62 percent from a year earlier to 2.2 billion yuan.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at 
 dboey@bloomberg.net  